We were a little bit careless.” Stuart Thomas scored a game-high 27 points and grabbed nine rebounds for the Mustangs. On Saturday, the Mustangs lost to to Cal State Dominguez Hills 58-56. Beason said his team’s play improved from Friday night, but it wasn’t enough. “Dominguez played a super game,” Beason said. Coby Naess led the Mustangs with 18 points, while Cal State Dominguez Hills’ Raymond Bennett scored a game-high 26 points. The Mustangs are now 13-6 overall, 3-3 in the CCAA. The Mustangs have eight games remaining in the CCAA regular season — three at home and five away. “It’s an uphill fight from now on,” Beason said. Getting along swimmingly...
